"Eliceche A.M., Corvalán S.M., Martínez P.","Environmental life cycle impact as a tool for process optimisation of a utility plant",2007,"Computers and Chemical Engineering","31","5-6",,"648","656",,,10.1016/j.compchemeng.2006.09.005,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-33847127022&partnerID=40&md5=661d31e78275ab8e9300540ac5c8d25c","Departamento de Ingeniería Química, Universidad Nacional del Sur, CONICET, Camino La Carrindanga km 7, 8000 Bahía Blanca, Argentina","Eliceche, A.M., Departamento de Ingeniería Química, Universidad Nacional del Sur, CONICET, Camino La Carrindanga km 7, 8000 Bahía Blanca, Argentina; Corvalán, S.M., Departamento de Ingeniería Química, Universidad Nacional del Sur, CONICET, Camino La Carrindanga km 7, 8000 Bahía Blanca, Argentina; Martínez, P., Departamento de Ingeniería Química, Universidad Nacional del Sur, CONICET, Camino La Carrindanga km 7, 8000 Bahía Blanca, Argentina","The purpose of this paper is to minimize environmental life cycle impact when a detail process modelling is available. A methodology is presented to calculate the optimum operating conditions of an ethylene process utility plant. The overall environmental impact is calculated as a weighted sum of global warming, acidification, eutrophication, photochemical oxidation, ozone depletion, human toxicity and ecotoxicity. The battery limits of the plant are extended to include the relevant environmental impacts corresponding to the imported electricity generated in thermoelectric, hydroelectric and nuclear plants. A mixed integer non-linear programming problem is formulated and solved in GAMS. Significant reductions in environmental impact particularly in global warming, the most relevant category, are obtained choosing the pressure and temperature of high, medium and low pressure steam headers together with the selection of optional drivers and boilers. Improvements achieved simultaneously in natural gas and electricity consumption and operating cost are also reported. © 2006 Elsevier Ltd. All rights reserved.","Environmental life cycle impact; Optimisation; Utility","Ecology; Environmental impact; Life cycle; Mathematical models; Optimization; Toxicity; Ecotoxicity; Environmental life cycle impact; Human toxicity; Process control; Ecology; Environmental impact; Life cycle; Mathematical models; Optimization; Process control; Toxicity",,,,,,"Azapagic, A., Clift, R., The application of life cycle assessment to process optimisation (1999) Computers and Chemical Engineering, 23, pp. 1509-1526; Brooke, A., Kendrick, D., Meeraus, A., Raman, R., (2003) GAMS development corporation. A user guide; Cabezas, H., Bare, J., Mallick, C., Pollution prevention with chemical process simulator: the generalised waste reduction (WAR) algorithm (1999) Computers and Chemical Engineering, 23, pp. 623-634; Dantus, M., High, K., Evaluation of waste minimization alternatives under uncertainty: a multi objective optimisation approach (1999) Computers and Chemical Engineering, 23, pp. 1493-1508; Elliot, T.C., (1989) Standard Handbook of Power Plant Engineering, , Me Graw Hill, New York; Finnveden, G., Nilsson, M., Johansson, J., Persson, A., Moberg, A., Carlsson, T., Strategic environmental assessment methodologies-applications within the energy sector (2003) Environmental Impact Assessment Review, 23, pp. 91-123; Fu, Y., Diwekar, U., Cost effective environmental control technology for utilities (2003) Advances in Environmental Research, 8, pp. 173-196; Gagnon, L., Bélanger, C., Uchiyama, Y., Life-cycle assessment of electricity options: The status of research in year 2001 (2002) Energy Policy, 30, pp. 1267-1278; Gagnon, L., van de Vate, J., Greenhouse gas Emissions from Hydropower (1997) Energy Policy, 25 (1), pp. 7-13; Hashim, H., Douglas, P., Elkamel, A., Croiset, E., Optimization model for energy planning CO2 emission considerations (2005) Industrial Engineering Chemical Resources, 44, pp. 879-890; Heijungs, R., Guinée, J.B., Huppes, G., Lankreijer, R.M., Udo de Haes, H.A., Wegener Sleeswijk, A., (1992) Environmental life cycle assessment of products I: guide and II: backgrounds, , CML, Leiden; Seinfeld, J.H., (1998) Atmospheric chemistry and physics of air pollution, , Wiley, New York; Smith, R.L., Mata, T., Young, D., Cabezas, H., Costa, C., Designing environmentally friendly chemical processes with fugitive and open emissions (2004) Journal of Cleaner Production, 12, pp. 125-129; Stefanis, S.K., Livingston, A., Pistikopoulos, E.N., Minimizing the environmental impact of process plants: a process systems methodology (1995) Computers and Chemical Engineering, 19. , pp. 39-34; Young, D., Scharp, R., Cabezas, H., The waste reduction (WAR) algorithm: environmental impact, energy consumption and engineering economic (2000) Waste Management, 20, pp. 605-615","Eliceche, A.M.; Departamento de Ingeniería Química, Universidad Nacional del Sur, CONICET, Camino La Carrindanga km 7, 8000 Bahía Blanca, Argentina; email: meliceche@plapiqui.edu.ar",,,,,,,,00981354,,CCEND,,"English","Comput. Chem. Eng.",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-33847127022
